    "Name": "Chrysaor HVT",
    "Details": "The Chryasaor Hovertank, named after a horse in Greek mythology, was heavily inspired by the similarly named Pegasus. Scarborough Manufacturing noted that the Pegasus had proven itself surprisingly effective in direct combat for a recon vehicle, though generally lacking sufficient ammunition for a prolonged battle. The Chryasaor maintains the same speed, but brings more armor, firepower, and ammo to the fight.\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Fusion: Expensive engine that works in a Vacuum.</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Movement: 8/12 hexes / 240/360 meters.</color></b>\n\n<color=#ffcc00><b>Armor:</b> Heavy Ferro-Fibrous\n<b>Structure:</b> Structure\n<b>Values       A        S  </b>\n<b>Front</b>       250     25\n<b>Left</b>         190     25\n<b>Right</b>       190     25\n<b>Rear</b>        150     25\n<b>Turret</b>      200     25\n\n<b>Total</b>      980    125</color>\n\n<color=#ff0000>Quirk: Improved Communications</color>",
